The paper deals with lower bounds for fundamental problems in data structures and algorithms, specifically SetDisjointness and SetIntersection. These problems are related to data structures and computational complexity, which are covered by the cs.DS and cs.CC sub-categories. The paper also discusses the tradeoff between preprocessing and query time, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper presents several applications of the new conditional lower bounds, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
